counter-style.doc:
The <strong><code>@counter-style</code></strong> <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/CSS">CSS</a> <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/CSS/At-rule">at-rule</a> lets you extend predefined list styles and define your own counter styles that are not part of the predefined set of styles. The <code>@counter-style</code> rule contains <a href="#descriptors">descriptors</a> defining how the counter value is converted into a string representation.
<div>
```css
@counter-style thumbs {
  system: cyclic;
  symbols: "\1F44D";
  suffix: " ";
}
ul {
  list-style: thumbs;
}
```
</div>
<p>While CSS provides many useful predefined counter styles, the <code>@counter-style</code> at-rule offers an open-ended method for creating counters. This at-rule caters to the needs of worldwide typography by allowing authors to define their own counter styles when the predefined styles don't fit their requirements.

