next-sibling_combinator.doc:
The <strong>next-sibling combinator</strong> (<code>+</code>) separates two selectors and matches the second element only if it <em>immediately</em> follows the first element, and both are children of the same parent <a href="$MDN_URL$/Web/API/Element"><code>element</code></a>.
<div>
```css
/* Paragraphs that come immediately after any image */
img + p {
  font-weight: bold;
}
```
</div>

